One thing you can do is fake a click on a pagination link.

For example:

```
$('#example').click(function(){
    $('.pagination a[rel="3"]').click();
});
```

In that example clicking an element with an ID of example with result in a click of a pagination link with a rel of 3 which will goto slide 4. Because JavaScript is creating and using the rel's in those links, 0 = 1. So just subtract 1 from whichever slide you want it to goto.

