Rather than modifying the slidesjs source, I wrote a little block of jQuery that replaces the numbers in the pagination widget with the content of the title attributes for each image slide. In my example I used the current version (version 3) of the slidesjs code but it will work with any version with a little fine tuning.

Create the slideshow as usual and then loop through the images and update the pagination widget:

``` javascript

       $(function() {

      // Start slideshow
      $('#slides').slidesjs({
        width: 940,
        height: 528
      });

      // Update pagination widget with titles from slide images
      $('#slides img').each(function() {
        var slidetitle = $(this).attr('title');
        var index = $(this).attr('slidesjs-index');
        $('.slidesjs-pagination li a[data-slidesjs-item='+index+']').text(slidetitle);
      });

    });
```

